1 Section 1. Chapter 422 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. To the extent that federal financial participation is available, the Director
4 shall include under Medicaid pursuant to 42 U.S.C. § 1396b(v)(2) and 42 C.F.R.
5 § 440.255 coverage for care that is necessary to treat an emergency medical
6 condition of a resident of this State who is less than 21 years of age and would
7 otherwise be ineligible for Medicaid solely because of his or her immigration
8 status. The coverage provided pursuant to this section must consist of coverage
9 for:
10 (a) Emergency medical transportation services directly relating to the
11 treatment of the emergency medical condition;
12 (b) Care to treat the emergency medical condition provided in an emergency
13 room or similar setting in a hospital or an independent center for emergency
14 medical care;
15 (c) Inpatient services provided to a person immediately following the
16 admission of the person from an emergency room, independent center for
17 emergency medical care, clinic or other similar setting where the person
18 originally sought care for his or her emergency medical condition, if the inpatient
19 services directly relate to the treatment of the emergency medical condition;
20 (d) If approved by the Department pursuant to subsection 3:
21 (1) Care that is provided in a facility for skilled nursing or other similar
22 facility for treatment in a community setting following the discharge of a person
23 from a hospital where the person was receiving inpatient services, if the care
24 directly relates to the emergency medical condition for which the person received
25 care before the discharge;
26 (2) Dialysis provided in a hospital or a facility for the treatment of
27 irreversible renal disease;
28 (3) [Care,] The transplant of bone marrow, if the person:
29 (I) Has been diagnosed with cancer;
30 (II) Is currently receiving treatment for the cancer; and
31 (III) Is a candidate for a bone marrow transplant;
32 (4) Other care that is medically necessary to treat any stage of cancer or
33 to prevent the recurrence of cancer, whether provided on an inpatient or
34 outpatient basis, including, without limitation, surgery, chemotherapy , [and]
35 radiation therapy, [that is necessary to treat cancer which is not in remission;]
36 targeted therapy and immunotherapy; and
37 [(4)] (5) The transplant of a kidney, if the person:
38 (I) Has been diagnosed with end-stage renal disease;
39 (II) Is receiving dialysis services; and
40 (III) Is a candidate for a kidney transplant; and

